The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Havala cuffs on terror suspect
                                                                                                               Havala cuffs on terror suspect
                            
	New Delhi, Sept. 25 (PTI): An Indian businessman, whom the US accuses of financing terror, was today booked by the Enforcement Directorate for allegedly running a havala operation worth Rs 5,000 crore.        
	Naresh Jain, who allegedly had links with underworld don Dawood Ibrahim and al Qaida, has been accused of being a havala mastermind. His operations are believed to be spread over Nigeria, Afghanistan, China and Pakistan among other countries.        
	Sleuths searched eight of his premises and claimed to have recovered unaccounted cash of Rs 60 lakh from his residence in north Delhi, sources said.         
	Papers showing havala transactions of several crores of rupees with several Pakistan- and Afghanistan-based persons and entities were also seized, the sources said.        
	The US department of homeland security and the UKs Serious Organised Crime Agency have accused him of laundering drug money for various terror groups.        
	The Enforcement Directorate also claimed that Jain, along with his brothers Bimal and Satpal, used to undertake havala operations for Dawood Ibrahim and al Qaida.                                                                                                                                                                            
